union , shipper agre to cut n.y. port cost the new york ship associ and intern longshoremen 's associ said they agre to cut cargo assess at the port of new york and new jersey by more than 50 pct on some labor intens cargo . the charg on cargo handl by union worker will be reduc to 2.85 dlr a ton from 5.85 dlr a ton , effect april one , accord to the agreement between the union and shipper . the assess are use to fund worker ' benefit . `` what were do is lower the price to get more bulk cargo flow through here , '' a spokesman for the new york ship associ said .